column20: Includes Illinois data for Sangamon River Forest Preserve, ISGS well CHAM-08-09B, ISGS well CHAM-08-09C, ISGS well CHAM-08-09A, ISGS well CHAM-08-09WT, and ISGS well CHAM-14-03B: [CRLF] * This dataset contains barometric pressure observations collected from a pressure transducer hanging within one of the wells at the Sangamon River Forest Preserve site. This data is to be used to provide atmospheric pressure measurements to correct the pressure transducer measurements monitoring water levels in the observation wells at this site. Data should be parsed by calendar year. [CRLF] * 171 foot well - This well was installed in 2008 to a depth of approximately 171 feet. The well is finished in a sand and gravel deposit. Information in this dataset will include water level observations from manual readings or transducers, as well as geologic descriptions, and other information related to the geology at the well or the construction of the observation well. Additional information may be saved that includes field notes or other metadata related to water well levels, data files, or other aspects of this well. [CRLF] * 69 foot well - This well was installed in 2008 to a depth of approximately 69 feet. The well is finished in a sand and gravel deposit. Information in this dataset will include water level observations from manual readings or transducers, as well as geologic descriptions, and other information related to the geology at the well or the construction of the observation well. Additional information may be saved that includes field notes or other metadata related to water well levels, data files, or other aspects of this well. [CRLF] * 260 ft well, ISGS well CHAM-08-09A) - This well was installed in 2008 at a depth of approximately 260 feet. The well is finished in a sand and gravel deposit. Information in this dataset will include water level observations from manual readings or transducers, as well as geologic descriptions, and other information related to the geology at the well or the construction of the observation well. Transducer data is intended to be parsed by calendar year. From 2011 through at least 2016, this well was included in the USGS Real-Time Groundwater Level Network for Illinois. All transducer data was collected by the USGS and has been downloaded and parsed. Additional information may be saved that includes field notes or other metadata related to water well levels, data files, or other aspects of this well. [CRLF] * 21 foot well - This well was installed in 2008 to a depth of approximately 21.5 feet. The well is finished in a glacial diamicton (till). Information in this dataset will include water level observations from manual readings or transducers, as well as geologic descriptions, and other information related to the geology at the well or the construction of the observation well. Transducer data is intended to be parsed by calendar year. From 2011 through at least 2016, this well was included in the USGS Real-Time Groundwater Level Network for Illinois. All transducer data was collected by the USGS and has been downloaded and parsed. Additional information may be saved that includes field notes or other metadata related to water well levels, data files, or other aspects of this well. [CRLF] * 12 foot well - This well was installed in 2014 to a depth of approximately 12 feet. The well is finished in a glacial diamicton (till). Information in this dataset will include water level observations from manual readings or transducers, as well as geologic descriptions, and other information related to the geology at the well or the construction of the observation well. column20: Land cover in the USand the CCW - The land cover data is collected annually from USDA for the whole US. The data can be downloaded here https://nassgeodata.gmu.edu/CropScape/. Data resolution is 30 *30 m. The available data period for both USRB and CCW is from 2008 till 2015

column3: IMLCZO -- GIS/Map Data -- Spatial and GIS Data -- Upper Sangamon River Basin, Illinois -- (2017-2017)
column20: Data Contains: [CRLF] * ISGS_geological survey of IL - This zip file includes several ArcGIS map from ISGS. Glacial boundary, Loess thickness, moraine boundary, bedrock topogrpahy, drift thickness, etc. [CRLF] * Soil_data_USRB_CCW - The original data is from USDA web soil survey (http://websoilsurvey.sc.egov.usda.gov/App/HomePage.htm). The uploaded files here are erosion factor and soil texture, which are converted from the soil survey index. [CRLF] * Previous measurement station - These sensor locations are previously installed inside USRB, including precipitation stations, sediment station, USGS stream station, Ameriflux tower, ISWS Stream and nutrient station, etc. [CRLF] * USLandcover in 2014 - Spatial and GIS Data. [CRLF] * GIS survey of Hydrology in USRB - This zip folder includes several files: 1. Major tributaries 2. NHD Flowlines 3. Stream order of major streams 4. Waterbody 5. Watershed boundary. [CRLF] * USstreams - This dataset contains the streams from NHD (USGS national map viewer) and from ISGS (major tributaries). [CRLF] * USBoundaries - This dataset contains county , watershed , glacial, and moraine boundaries.

column3: IMLCZO -- GIS/Map Data, LiDAR -- Spatial and GIS Data -- Upper Sangamon River Basin, Illinois -- (2017-2017)
column20: Data Contains: [CRLF] * USRB_LiDAR_DEM.zip - 1.2 meter DEM of Upper Sangamon River Basin. QA/QC: Yes. [CRLF] * USRB_10m_DEM.zip - 10 meter DEM of Upper Sangamon River Basin. QA/QC: Yes, USRB_30m_DEM_NAD16.zip - 30 meter DEM of Upper Sangamon River Basin with NAD16 projection. QA/QC: Yes. [CRLF] * SRB_30m_DEM_GCS83.zip - 30 meter DEM of Upper Sangamon River Basin with GCS83 projection. QA/QC: Yes. [CRLF] * USDEM - This dataset contains 30m DEM, 10m DEM and LiDAR DEM (1.2m).

column3: IMLCZO -- Surface Water Chemistry -- Surface Water -- Monticello, Illinois -- (2017-2018)
column20: Site ID: #111 Monticello Datasets contain water quality data collected by two YSI sondes deployed in PVC tubes mounted on the slope of the downstream side of the W. Bridge Street bridge in Monticello, IL near USGS River Station 05572000. Coordinates: 40deg 1'51.37N 88deg35'18.32W WGS84 -YSI 6600EDS-O sonde Sensors: 6560 Conductivity/Temperature probe, 6136 Turbidity probe Data collected (direct): temperature (*C), conductivity (mS/cm), turbidity (NTU) Data collection start: 03/24/2017 (currently deployed) -YSI 600OMS-O sonde Sensors: Integrated conductivity/temperature probe, 6150+ ROX DO probe Data collected (direct): temperature (*C), conductivity (mS/cm), dissolved oxygen (mg/L) Data collection start: 04/20/2017 (currently deployed) -Sondes cannot be deployed if stage drops below ~5.5ft at Monticello as the sensors will not be submerged. -Data collection interval: 03/24/2017 - 08/4/2017 every 30 minutes; changed to every 15 minutes on 08/4/2017 to match collection frequency of USGS gaging station 05572000 at Monticello: https://waterdata.usgs.gov/il/nwis/uv?site_no=05572000. Between 08/21/2017-11/30/2017 there were few rain events and stage was consistently between 4-5 ft; sondes were deployed for 30-45 min periods to gather some data during this dry season.
